<recipe>
<title>
Fresh Corn Salsa
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 15 minutes
COURSE: Appetizer
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: corn, salsa
SERVINGS: 4
</details>
<ingredients>
2 ears fresh sweet corn
1 jalepe&#241;o* finely diced
1/4 cup finely chopped red onion
1/4 cup cilantro chopped
2 tablespoons fresh lime juice
1 clove garlic finely minced
pinches Couple salt
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Remove kernels from ears of corn.
In a medium bowl, toss together corn kernels, jalape&#241;o, onion, cilantro, lime juice, garlic, and salt.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>